  <section class="page-header">
    <h1 data-aos="fade-up">Decentralised Renewable Energy</h1>
    <p data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">How distributed solar and renewable systems are transforming energy access in Africa.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Article content -->
  <main class="article-content px-6 py-12" data-aos="fade-up">
    <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-6">By Timon Rowntree | January 2026</p>

    <p>
      Decentralised renewable energy systems provide communities with energy independence and resilience. These systems reduce reliance on central grids, offer faster deployment, and can be tailored to local needs, providing electricity for households, businesses, and public services.
    </p>

    <h2>Localized Energy Solutions</h2>
    <p>
      By implementing small-scale solar, wind, and hybrid systems, communities can generate their own power. Local operators are trained in maintenance and monitoring, creating jobs and technical skills while ensuring the system operates efficiently.
    </p>

    <h2>Resilience and Sustainability</h2>
    <p>
      Decentralised systems minimize the impact of grid outages and support sustainable energy usage. With proper design and quality components, these systems offer reliable electricity, reduce carbon footprints, and enable economic growth in underserved regions.
    </p>

    <h2>Scaling Across the Continent</h2>
    <p>
      Successful examples from West and East Africa show that decentralised energy can scale sustainably. With careful planning, community engagement, and innovative financing models, these projects expand access to clean energy across rural and peri-urban areas.
    </p>

